          "title": "Barbarian",
          "year": 2022,
          "note": "Zach Cregger's horror movie is set in a Detroit Airbnb. It opens as double-booked-rental dread, swerves into a Justin Long cancellation comedy, then flashes back to the 1980s serial killer who built the tunnels underneath. Georgina Campbell plays Tess. Bill Skarsgard plays the too-reassuring stranger. The monster in the sub-basement is called 'Mother.'"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "interview",
      "heading": "Zach Cregger on 'Barbarian'",
      "guest": "Zach Cregger on",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Barbarian",
          "year": 2022,
          "note": "Cregger, formerly of the comedy troupe The Whitest Kids U' Know, wrote it blind in his garage and stopped at 45 pages when the giant naked woman appeared. The 1980s flashback and the old man in the bed were a later retrofit, prompted by a producer's one note before he ghosted. Financed at ~$4.5M through Roy Lee and New Regency after the original backer died on the eve of the shoot."
        }
      ]
